## 🔧 Universal Standards (All Code)

### Naming Conventions
- **Variables**: camelCase (`const userName = "John"`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`const MAX_RETRIES = 3`)
- **Functions**: camelCase with verb (`function fetchUser()`)
- **Classes**: PascalCase (`class UserManager {}`)
- **Files**: Match export type (camelCase for utils, PascalCase for classes)
- **Database**: snake_case (`user_id`, `created_at`)

### Code Quality
- ✅ Use `const` by default, `let` when needed, never `var`
- ✅ One responsibility per function/class/module
- ✅ Functions under 50 lines, files under 400 lines
- ✅ Self-documenting code with clear names
- ✅ JSDoc comments for public APIs
- ✅ No commented-out code

### Error Handling (MANDATORY)
- ✅ Always use try-catch for error-prone operations
- ✅ Throw meaningful error messages
- ✅ Log errors with context
- ✅ Handle async/await errors properly
- ✅ Never silently catch errors

### Performance Rules
- **API responses**: < 200ms (p95)
- **Database queries**: < 100ms (p95)
- **Page loads**: < 2.5s (LCP)
- **Bundle size**: < 100KB (gzipped)
- **Test coverage**: > 70%
- **Memory**: Stable, no leaks
- **CPU**: < 80% during normal operations

### Security (MANDATORY)
- ✅ Validate ALL user input
- ✅ Use parameterized database queries (never string concatenation)
- ✅ Never log passwords or sensitive data
- ✅ Use HTTPS in production
- ✅ Implement authentication/authorization
- ✅ Use rate limiting for APIs
- ✅ Sanitize output to prevent XSS
- ✅ Implement CORS properly

