## 🟨 JavaScript (ES6+) Standards

### Key Rules (from javascript-stack.mdc)
- ✅ Use async/await, not callbacks or promise chains
- ✅ Implement proper error handling with try-catch
- ✅ Use arrow functions for callbacks
- ✅ Debounce/throttle event handlers
- ✅ Memoize expensive computations
- ✅ Clean up event listeners (prevent memory leaks)
- ✅ Use named exports (tree-shakeable)
- ✅ No global variable pollution
- ✅ Avoid deeply nested code

### Code Example Pattern
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT
const userEmail = "user@example.com";
const MAX_RETRIES = 3;

function calculateTotal(items) {
  try {
    return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Calculation failed:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}

async function fetchUser(id) {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${id}`);
    if (!response.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}`);
    return await response.json();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Fetch failed:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}

// ✗ NEVER DO THIS
var oldStyle = 10;
function badError() { return something.catch(); }
fetch('/api').then(r => r.json());  // No error handling
```

