## ⚛️ React Standards

### Key Rules (from react-stack.mdc)
- ✅ Use functional components only (never class components)
- ✅ Proper useEffect dependency arrays
- ✅ Custom hooks for reusable logic
- ✅ React.memo for expensive components
- ✅ useMemo for expensive computations
- ✅ useCallback for function props
- ✅ Code splitting and lazy loading
- ✅ Unique, stable keys in lists
- ✅ Controlled form components
- ✅ Error boundaries for error handling

### Component Structure
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT
export function UserProfile({ userId, onClose }) {
  const [user, setUser] = React.useState(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = React.useState(true);

  React.useEffect(() => {
    let isMounted = true;
    fetchUser(userId)
      .then(data => isMounted && setUser(data))
      .finally(() => isMounted && setLoading(false));
    return () => { isMounted = false; };
  }, [userId]);

  if (loading) return <Spinner />;
  return <div>{user?.name}</div>;
}

// ✗ NEVER DO THIS
class UserProfile extends React.Component { }  // Old pattern
const list = items.map(i => <Item />);  // No key!
const obj = {};  // New object every render
```

