## 🗄️ PostgreSQL Standards

### Key Rules (from postgresql-stack.mdc)
- ✅ JSONB for semi-structured data
- ✅ ENUM types for fixed value sets
- ✅ Window functions for analytics
- ✅ Full-text search for text columns
- ✅ CTEs for complex queries
- ✅ Materialized views for expensive queries
- ✅ GIN indexes for JSONB/arrays
- ✅ EXPLAIN ANALYZE for query optimization
- ✅ Regular VACUUM ANALYZE maintenance
- ✅ Parameterized queries (prevent SQL injection)

### Advanced Pattern
```sql
-- ✅ CORRECT - JSONB with index
CREATE TABLE users (
  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  profile_data JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_users_profile ON users USING GIN(profile_data);

-- ✅ Window function
SELECT id, amount,
  SUM(amount) OVER (ORDER BY date) as running_total
FROM orders;

-- ✗ NEVER DO THIS
profile_data TEXT;  -- Use JSONB instead
status VARCHAR(20);  -- Use ENUM instead
```

