## 🖥️ Electron Standards

### Key Rules (from electron-stack.mdc)
- ✅ Preload script for security (contextIsolation: true)
- ✅ IPC for main/renderer communication
- ✅ Content Security Policy headers
- ✅ No nodeIntegration in renderer
- ✅ Input validation on IPC handlers
- ✅ File path validation (prevent traversal)
- ✅ Logging for debugging
- ✅ Auto-update mechanism
- ✅ Graceful shutdown
- ✅ Error handling for all IPC calls

### Security Pattern
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT - Main process
new BrowserWindow({
  webPreferences: {
    preload: path.join(__dirname, 'preload.js'),
    contextIsolation: true,      // ✅ Enable
    enableRemoteModule: false,   // ✅ Disable
    sandbox: true,               // ✅ Enable
    nodeIntegration: false       // ✅ Disable
  }
});

// ✅ IPC with validation
ipcMain.handle('save-file', async (event, fileName, content) => {
  if (!fileName || typeof content !== 'string') {
    throw new Error('Invalid input');
  }
  const safePath = path.join(app.getPath('documents'), fileName);
  if (!safePath.startsWith(app.getPath('documents'))) {
    throw new Error('Invalid path');
  }
  await fs.promises.writeFile(safePath, content);
  return { success: true };
});

// ✗ NEVER DO THIS
nodeIntegration: true;  // DANGEROUS!
contextIsolation: false;  // UNSAFE!
ipcMain.handle('save', (event, path, content) => {  // No validation!
  fs.writeFileSync(path, content);  // Path traversal risk!
});
```

