## 🔗 Database Common Standards

### Key Rules (from database-common-stack.mdc)
- ✅ Universal naming: snake_case for tables/columns
- ✅ Constraints: PK, FK, UNIQUE, CHECK
- ✅ Transactions for related operations
- ✅ Backup/restore strategy
- ✅ Performance targets defined
- ✅ Security: parameterized queries
- ✅ Both MySQL and PostgreSQL covered
- ✅ Database selection guidance

### Pattern
```sql
-- ✅ CORRECT - Both MySQL & PostgreSQL
CREATE TABLE orders (
  id BIGINT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
  user_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
  amount DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  
  CONSTRAINT fk_orders_user_id 
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(id)
);

CREATE INDEX idx_orders_user_id ON orders(user_id);

-- ✅ Parameterized queries
SELECT * FROM orders WHERE user_id = ?;  -- Safe

-- ✗ NEVER DO THIS
SELECT * FROM orders WHERE user_id = '${userId}';  -- SQL injection!
```

